The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 1st ACC womens meet

A STAFF REPORTER

Calcutta: Eight teams will vie for honours in the first Asian Cricket Council (ACC) womens tournament to be held in Johor Baru, Malaysia from July 11-18. In the build-up to the meet, Hong Kong will host China in their first-ever cricket match to be played in Shenzhen on June 24, according to a press release. 

The historic match-up between China and Hong Kong to be held in Shenzhen University Stadium will act as the ideal appetiser ahead of the main event . 

The teams for the eight-nation tournament are divided into two groups (A and B). Group A comprises Hong Kong, Malaysia, Thailand and Nepal while UAE, Bangladesh, Singapore and China are in Group B. . 

Explaining the significance of the upcoming action, chairperson of the ACC womens committee, Shubhangi Kulkarni said: We have already seen enthusiasm and interest among women cricketers in the region and now this tournament will allow them to show their potential. 

THE SCHEDULE 

July 11 Hong Kong vs Malaysia and Bangladesh vs UAE. July 12 Thailand vs Nepal and Singapore vs China. July 13 Hong Kong vs Thailand and Bangladesh vs Singapore. July 14 Malaysia vs Nepal and UAE vs China. July 15 Hong Kong vs Nepal and Bangladesh vs China. July 16 Malaysia vs Thailand and UAE vs Singapore. July 17 Semi-finals (A1 vs B2) and (B1 vs A2). July 18 Final 




